1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:13,000
Dashboard. Click Run profit scan to refresh the margin scan.

2
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:29,000
The Action center summarizes catalog health, issues to review, and inventory risk.

3
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:45,000
Click the Fix first card area to focus on the suggested minimum price and next action.

4
00:00:45,000 --> 00:01:02,000
Click Export full fix list. Margin Sentinel stays read-only and never changes Shopify prices automatically.

5
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Click a finding row to see the product that needs attention.

6
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:27,000
The row shows SKU, price, cost, margin, inventory risk, and suggested minimum price.

7
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Click the suggested price and next-action columns to show what the merchant should do next.

8
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:50,000
This makes the scan actionable instead of just reporting a number.

9
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:03,000
Pricing page. Click each plan to show what the merchant gets.

10
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:18,000
Free includes a small scan and CSV export. Starter unlocks larger scans, supplier import, what-if, and alerts.

11
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Growth is for bigger catalogs and priority support.

12
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Click Start 14-day trial. Paid plans are handled through Shopify billing.

13
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:55,000
Supplier import. Click the CSV area to show the accepted columns: variant ID, inventory item ID, SKU, and cost.

14
00:02:55,000 --> 00:03:11,000
Click the matched count. The preview confirms which rows match Shopify variants before saving.

15
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Click the What-if controls to model supplier cost increases.

16
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:42,000
This helps merchants respond before low-margin products continue selling.

17
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:53,000
Export. Click Download findings CSV to create the saved fix list.

18
00:03:53,000 --> 00:04:07,000
The CSV includes issue type, product, cost source, margin gap, inventory risk, and next action.

19
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:18,000
Actionable next steps are clear: raise price, reduce cost, fix missing cost, or review discount rules.

20
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:26,000
That is the core promise: catch margin leaks before products keep selling.
